text: Starkville is a city in, and the county seat of, Oktibbeha County, Mississippi, United States. Mississippi State University, the state's land- grant institution and a public flagship university, is located just outside the city limits in unincorporated Oktibbeha County. The population was 24,360 in 2020. ==References== Category:Cities in Mississippi Category:County seats in Mississippi
title: Starkville, Mississippi
